My son said, “mom! I’m going to play the piano and you are going to dance!” 

There was ZERO doubt in his mind of his ability to play and so much excitement.. like it was THE best idea EVER. 

And it definitely was the best idea ever. We danced and laughed until our cheeks hurt.

I usually share my work out time with this little squirt. 

I was just barely going to write, some mornings are better than others… But when she’s a little more clingy, that doesn’t make it worse. That was just my thought about it, right @seantayhall ?

Did my workout go as planned this morning? No. And it was beautiful! And I loved it! 

Babies are actually a perfect added weight to your work out. 

It keeps your chest up, your tail bone tucked, it challenges your balance just a little bit more and it lets you smile. 

Try it and tag me.

Especially when you are taking a pre-workout full of disguised CRAP (aka..sugar…aka.. poison…even if it’s “the natural kind”) because then your workout is getting you pumped! It is doing the job.. but your workout is now just working off your pre-workout 😅🤪

Alignment in Warrior 1!

Some tips:

Front leg— 
•Feet are on different tracks
•knee over or behind ankle

Hips—
•Square them to the front of your mat
•Lift hips up
•Tuck the tailbone
•Engage your core
•Lift pelvic floor

Back leg—
•Weight is on the PINKY toe side of the whole foot
•Internally rotate your femur / thigh

Arms—
•Lift upward
•Gaze up

•SMILE!

OVER HALF WAY THERE!!!

Woke up with a smile on my face to take on this week!
I leave for the mountains of Montana in a number of days so I’m going to get this goal SOLID before I leave!

Life is what you make it. I’m learning that. I’m learning that I can create time for anything that is truly important to me. 

My August has been full of being on the phone a LOT. In fact, the other day my daughter said, “Mom? Will you not be on the phone at all on my birthday?” 🥹
Yes, babe. Yes. 

And then we reminded each other why I’m doing this and how she can join me and be a part of it. 

My August has also been so full of really being so present with my kids and blocking out times without my phone and spending a little more time beside their beds during bedtime. My kids are learning to play with each other deeper when mom is a little more occupied. 

We are all learning how to create room for something bigger and it’s brought so much meaning to my month.

We created a team with young adults and called it ProMovement. (It was the best team!!) We also created a slogan for it: DREAM BIG, LIVE BIG, GIVE BIG. 

This ProMovement team… we dreamt BIIIIG. We had all the vision in the world!!

Then my husband and I took a break to build another business. Through this, we have been able to live so big. Live in ways others can’t and we feel so blessed!! (We blame it all on God).

One of my favorite things about yoga is that you can always depend on it. It’s always there, in every sense of the word. 

Your breath- the actual heart of yoga. You can always come to it. Right now, as you are reading this, take a deep breath. 
One of my favorite quotes says, “taking a deep breath is like giving yourself a big hug.” That’s yoga. 

Your physical asanas- you don’t need anything, not even a mat. In fact, I prefer no mat. I can move freely and don’t feel constricted to a space at all.

You don’t need to be “good” at it, you don’t need to go to a class, just be. Breathe. Move. 

Let it flow from within. 

I think this world is really good at telling us to go outward- ask questions on the internet or social media, go read a book, go listen to a podcast, go talk to all the people, on and on..

While those are great and learning is unmatched, you have divinity within your soul just by being here and having a body to house your spirit. I personally believe Goddliness is in every cell of our being. You have the light, you were born with the light. No matter what. 

🙏 the light in me honors and loves the light in you.✨

I’ve shared this on here before but this bread is life.

It came into my life when I needed something to help me get through my first miscarriage and it has been a huge blessing to me and others ever since. 

I have now had two more miscarriages in the last three months, one at 2 weeks and the next at 6 weeks, in August and October. This bread is still helping me through all of them while also helping some good friends get through some health challenges. 

I hear things like, “things in life don’t matter..” and I disagree. True, they probably don’t hold as much value as humans but I hold some things in life so close and this bread and the process of making it is one of them. 

Thanks, flour, salt and water. 🫶

Yoga feels like dancing to me. That’s why I love it.
